%p If you feel terrible you don’t have to take sedatives or stimulants to feel better.
%p First, try #{@type.first.get.ing} something #{@type.first.tempting}. Although you rarely feel #{@type.first.empty} that doesn’t mean you don’t need more #{@type.first.energy}. Getting more #{@type.first.energy} should always be your first priority.
%p If that doesn’t work, try #{@type.second.achieve.ing} a #{@type.second.easy} #{@type.second.goal}; it will distract you from the #{@type.second.hard} #{@type.second.goal} you should not be trying to #{@type.second.achieve}. Avoiding unnecessarily #{@type.second.hard} #{@type.second.goal.s} should  be your second priority.
%p If that doesn’t work, try #{@type.third.get.ing} something #{@type.third.basic}. Although you don’t need more #{@type.third.energy} that doesn’t mean you don’t need more #{@type.third.necessities}. Getting rid of unwanted #{@type.third.reserves} doesn’t mean you can neglect your #{@type.third.strength} when you feel #{@type.third.empty}.
%p If all else fails, try #{@type.fourth.achieve.ing} a #{@type.fourth.hard} #{@type.fourth.goal}; having to #{@type.fourth.achieve} all the #{@type.fourth.part.s} will keep you #{@type.fourth.drain.ing} and using your #{@type.fourth.strength} will keep your #{@type.fourth.power} busy and happy.
